    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="910"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/11–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative in Korea</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-09">November 9,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. Cite <gloss target="#t_Zpol1">Zpol</gloss> 1876. Pass Paris <gloss
                        target="#t_Gadel1">GADel</gloss> for Jacobs.<note n="1" xml:id="d910fn1"
                        >This was done the same day.</note> Following message from President Rhee to
                    Chang Myun, Korean delegation Paris: “Due to recent uprising and also to
                    continued propaganda stories coming from north, people feel nervous for fear
                    that Red Army might march down south moment the American forces pull out. If
                    necessary make formal appeal to <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Assembly to
                    adopt resolution requesting US to retain even a token force in south for time
                    being”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
